$ Windows Settings: Choose default apps by file type

*Choose default apps by file type* allows to associate a file type (→ development/filename-extensions[file extension]) with an application
(program → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/EXE[executable]).

The *Choose default apps by file type* can be reached via the *Default apps* settings page and then clicking on the *Choose default apps by file type* link. On the command line, the *Default apps* setting page can be reached with
code {
C:\> → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/start ms-settings:defaultapps
code }

gh|Windows-Pics|/ms-settings/defaultapps/Choose-default-apps-by-file-type.png||

Apparently, these default settings are stored in the → Windows/registry under
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Explorer/FileExts[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\FileExts`]

sa:
  The → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] commands → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/assoc[`assoc`] and
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/ftype[`ftype`].
